      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content
</head>
         <p>The collection contains the manuscripts for the following poems and short stories:  <title render="doublequote">Old ace,</title> 
            <title render="doublequote">Dead dancer,</title> 
            <title render="doublequote">Continuous performance,</title> 
            <title render="doublequote">The husbandman [A green bough],</title> 
            <title render="doublequote">L'apres-midi d'un faune,</title> 
            <title render="doublequote">The lilacs,</title> 
            <title render="doublequote">Music dying languidly in darkness,</title> and <title render="doublequote">One way to catch a horse,</title> as well as untitled fragments and a brief outline for parts of <title render="italic">Sanctuary.</title>  The collection also contains several sketches including a Japanese woman, soldiers and an airplane; and <title render="doublequote">Landing in luck,</title> as printed in the <title render="italic">Oxford Eagle</title> (Miss.) in 1919.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement>
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The collection is in two series : I. Manuscripts. II.
         Miscellaneous</p>
      </arrangement>
